JavaScriptExecutor Interface

	What Is JavaScriptExecutor:

		Selenium WebDriver API provides the Ability to execute JavaScript code with the browser window. this is a very useful feature when tests need to interact with the page using javaScript

		Using this API, client-side JavaScript code can also be tested using Selenium Webdriver.

		Selenium WebDriver provides a JavaScriptExecutor interface that can be used to exclude arbitrary JavaScript code within the contest of the browser

	What is It For?

		JavaScriptExecutor is an interface that allows us to execute JavaScript code as part of our selenium script.

		if something doesn't work n Selenium, we can use JavaScriptExecutor to perform webpage actions such as scroll, click, moveMouse, etc.
